        "action": "Remove single person protest clauses in Police, Crime, Sentencing & Courts Bill",
        "additional_details": "These clauses relating to single person protests are draconian in nature and are designed to stifle legitimate protest. \r\n\r\nSuch measures have no place in a democracy",
        "background": "The Government\u2019s new Police, Crime, Sentencing and Courts Bill contains clauses designed specifically to stifle single individuals legitimately protesting. These clauses should be removed from the Bill before it becomes law",
